commentTextItems.html: pulled forward of square, South Africa are the Wills International Cup World Champions

commentPostTextItems.html: a little scare in the middle of the innings, but the target was simply never going to be too hard
extravagant presentation ceremony to come, sizable fires bein lit all around the stadium
*the* song was sung (mimed) complete with unchoreographed dance routine
crowd now chanting something, maybe "Bang-la-desh"
the S1Ws are escorting the Prime Minister ontop the field
Ravi Shastri making a long list of thank yous
I think this presentation is going to take a while
umpires get a trophy each, and the referee gets one as well, head groundsman gets an award
Lara comes to collect the award, says "all credit to the South Africans", thought 275 would be a good total, gets a cheer for mentioning that it's been a good crowd
and the Man of the Match is.... Jacques Kallis
now Crnje and South Africa come up to collect their trophies
and now Cronje is up to collect "the big one", presented by the PM
says the trophy is very happy
erm, very heavy rather, and he's very happy
says Wallace has played very well
another cheer for mentioning the crowds have been fantastic
no Man of the Series award given
SA pose for a photo
and then go for a lap of honour
and the SA manager takes a big tumble over the rope... hoho
there's an army of kids following them
and that pretty much ends CricInfo's live coverage from Dhaka
If you want to send feedback about the tournament commentary, the address is travis@cricket.org
remember, your hate only makes me stronger
Thank you and good night
